unparsed_output: "Atherosclerosis" is the title of point number 10 in the document. It is a disease in which there is a thickening and narrowing of the arteries (major blood vessels). It deposits fat, cholesterol and other materials in the inner layer of the arterial wall interferes with the normal blood flow and the nourishment of the tissues. Atherosclerosis is often called "hardening of the arteries" (arteriosclerosis) and is the basic cause of most heart attacks and strokes.
